{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1778976806909,"sessionID":"ses_1ccb84d98ffeWH3ShOq9EHPmcq","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_knX1mGDanN2OG8K9UsdtaTuC","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/__issue_context__.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"body\": \"**Preferred term label:**\\nparotid gland ducto-acinar\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nEaster QT, et al. Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis. Nat Commun. 2024 Jun 14;15(1):5016. doi: 10.1038/s41467-024-49037-y. PMID: 38876998; PMCID: PMC11178863; https://doi.org/10.48539/HBM632.GTVR.643\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\nUBERON:0001831  parotid gland\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n0000-0002-2999-0103\\n\\n---------------\\n**Preferred term label:**\\ngingival attachment\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nEaster QT, et al. Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis. Nat Commun. 2024 Jun 14;15(1):5016. doi: 10.1038/s41467-024-49037-y. PMID: 38876998; PMCID: PMC11178863; https://doi.org/10.48539/HBM632.GTVR.643\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\nUBERON:0001828  gingiva\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n0000-0002-2999-0103\\n\\n---------------\\n**Preferred term label:**\\nsublingual gland ducto-acinar\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nEaster QT, et al. Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis. Nat Commun. 2024 Jun 14;15(1):5016. doi: 10.1038/s41467-024-49037-y. PMID: 38876998; PMCID: PMC11178863; https://doi.org/10.48539/HBM632.GTVR.643\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\nUBERON:0001832  sublingual gland\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n0000-0002-2999-0103\\n\\n---------------\\n**Preferred term label:**\\nsubmandibular gland ducto-acinar\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nEaster QT, et al. Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis. Nat Commun. 2024 Jun 14;15(1):5016. doi: 10.10... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n3:   \"comments\": [\n4:     {\n5:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87mOcu4\",\n6:       \"author\": {\n7:         \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n8:       },\n9:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n10:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please analyze these terms, provide a plan for how you will add them to the ontology, check for existing naming conventions and design patterns for similar terms\",\n11:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-06T20:59:48Z\",\n12:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n13:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n14:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n15:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n16:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-3862547384\",\n17:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": true\n18:     },\n19:     {\n20:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87mOfoJ\",\n21:       \"author\": {\n22:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n23:       },\n24:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n25:       \"body\": \"## Analysis of Term Requests\\n\\nI've analyzed the four term requests and the reference publication. Here's my plan for adding these terms to the ontology:\\n\\n### **Terms Requested:**\\n1. **parotid gland ducto-acinar** (parent: UBERON:0001831 parotid gland)\\n2. **gingival attachment** (parent: UBERON:0001828 gingiva)\\n3. **sublingual gland ducto-acinar** (parent: UBERON:0001832 sublingual gland)\\n4. **submandibular gland ducto-acinar** (parent: UBERON:0001736 submandibular gland)\\n\\n### **Key Findings:**\\n\\n#### 1. **Existing Ontology Coverage**\\n- All three salivary glands (parotid, sublingual, submandibular) are well-represented in UBERON\\n- Each has associated ducts, epithelium, mesenchyme, and developmental terms\\n- Gingiva (UBERON:0001828) exists with several subclasses including gingival epithelium\\n- **No existing \\\"ducto-acinar\\\" or \\\"acinar\\\" substructure terms** for salivary glands found\\n\\n#### 2. **Reference Publication Context**\\n- PMID:38876998 (Easter et al., Nature Communications 2024) is titled \\\"Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis\\\"\\n- The paper focuses on periodontitis and tooth-associated keratinocytes using single-cell RNA sequencing\\n- While cited for all terms, this paper is primarily about gingival/periodontal biology rather than salivary gland anatomy\\n\\n#### 3. **Anatomical Background - Ducto-Acinar Structures**\\nBased on salivary gland anatomy literature:\\n- Salivary glands have a fundamental **acinar-ductal unit** structure\\n- Acini are secretory end pieces that produce saliva\\n- The ductal system includes intercalated, striated, and excretory ducts\\n- \\\"Ducto-acinar\\\" likely refers to the integrated functional unit of ducts and acini\\n\\n#### 4. **Design Pattern Considerations**\\n\\n**Option A: Compositional Pattern (part_of)**\\n- Create terms like \\\"ducto-acinar unit\\\" as anatomical structures\\n- Use intersection_of with part_of relationships\\n- Example: interse... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n26:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-06T21:03:32Z\",\n27:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n28:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n29:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n30:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n31:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-3862559241\",\n32:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n33:     },\n34:     {\n35:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87opxl-\",\n36:       \"author\": {\n37:         \"login\": \"zhengj2007\"\n38:       },\n39:       \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n40:       \"body\": \"\\n@dragon-ai-agent please address:\\n\\nHere are the answers to your questions and concerns:\\n\\n1. We are defining the “ducto-acinar” FTU as the combined acinar–ductal functional unit of human salivary glands (option \\\"a\\\")_. Specifically, this refers to the structural-functional module composed of secretory acini together with their contiguous ductal segments (intercalated and striated ducts, and proximal collecting ducts where applicable). Importantly, this FTU is not limited to epithelial components alone. Our definition includes the associated stromal and vascular microenvironment that supports secretion, modification, and transport. In other words, this is a multicellular functional tissue unit.\\n--This definition aligns with the HRA concept of FTUs as repeating structural-functional modules that integrate epithelial, stromal, and vascular compartments. It is not intended to denote a specific transitional anatomical interface (acini–duct junction only) nor a transcriptomically defined cell population. These terms are intended for human anatomy only and are being anchored to HRA spatial coordinates. \\n\\nWe need \\\"ducto-acinar\\\" added in uberon. In classic literature, the ducto-acinar unit is sometimes called the \\\"salivon\\\" -- think of it relative to a hydrangea plant. The ductoacinar unit or salivon is one bulb and a stem. The salivary gland is the entire plant. Separating duct and acinar in this case would be like separating the flowers from their woody stem before connecting the branches that eventually connect to the main stem and then roots. \\n\\n2. For the gingival attachment term, the intended meaning corresponds to the entire dentogingival/periodontal attachment apparatus. Thus, among the proposed options, the closest answer is (c): the entire attachment apparatus. We agree that “gingival attachment” can be ambiguous in periodontal anatomy. If helpful for ontology precision, we would support renaming or clarifying the label to reflect that th... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n41:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-15T04:50:00Z\",\n42:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": true,\n43:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n44:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n45:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n46:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-3903265150\",\n47:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n48:     },\n49:     {\n50:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87o2aUO\",\n51:       \"author\": {\n52:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n53:       },\n54:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n55:       \"body\": \"Hello @zhengj2007,\\n\\nI'm reviewing your new term requests for issue #3657. I need some clarification on these terms before proceeding:\\n\\n## Questions about the \\\"ducto-acinar\\\" terms:\\n\\n1. **Parotid gland ducto-acinar**\\n2. **Sublingual gland ducto-acinar**\\n3. **Submandibular gland ducto-acinar**\\n\\nThe reference provided (PMID:38876998 - Easter et al. 2024) focuses on periodontal tissues and tooth-associated keratinocytes, but does not appear to describe ducto-acinar structures in salivary glands. Additionally, \\\"ducto-acinar\\\" is not a standard anatomical term I can find in the literature.\\n\\n**Could you please clarify:**\\n- What do these \\\"ducto-acinar\\\" terms specifically refer to anatomically?\\n- Are these referring to the transition zone between ducts and acini in salivary glands?\\n- Is there a different reference that specifically describes these structures?\\n- Are these cell types or anatomical structures that were identified in the HubMap dataset referenced by https://doi.org/10.48539/HBM632.GTVR.643?\\n\\n## About the \\\"gingival attachment\\\" term:\\n\\nThe paper does describe gingival epithelial structures, but I want to confirm - is \\\"gingival attachment\\\" referring to:\\n- The junctional epithelium (the specialized epithelium that directly attaches to the tooth surface)?\\n- The entire epithelial attachment apparatus?\\n- Something else specific to the HubMap analysis?\\n\\nUnderstanding the precise anatomical meaning will help me create accurate term definitions with the appropriate logical relationships.\\n\\nThank you!\\n\\n@dragon-ai-agent\",\n56:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-16T05:50:14Z\",\n57:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n58:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n59:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n60:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n61:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-3906577678\",\n62:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n63:     },\n64:     {\n65:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87tXIJN\",\n66:       \"author\": {\n67:         \"login\": \"zhengj2007\"\n68:       },\n69:       \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n70:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please propose UBERON parent term and definition of \\\"ducto-acinar\\\" based on the information I provided:\\n\\nWe are defining the “ducto-acinar” FTU as the combined acinar–ductal functional unit of human salivary glands (option \\\"a\\\")_. Specifically, this refers to the structural-functional module composed of secretory acini together with their contiguous ductal segments (intercalated and striated ducts, and proximal collecting ducts where applicable). Importantly, this FTU is not limited to epithelial components alone. Our definition includes the associated stromal and vascular microenvironment that supports secretion, modification, and transport. In other words, this is a multicellular functional tissue unit.\\n--This definition aligns with the HRA concept of FTUs as repeating structural-functional modules that integrate epithelial, stromal, and vascular compartments. It is not intended to denote a specific transitional anatomical interface (acini–duct junction only) nor a transcriptomically defined cell population. These terms are intended for human anatomy only and are being anchored to HRA spatial coordinates.\\n\\nAdditionally, I  got the following information when searched “ducto-acinar”:\\nA salivary gland ducto-acinar unit is the functional, tree-like structure of salivary glands consisting of terminal acini (secretory end-pieces) that produce primary saliva, connected to a ductal system that modifies this fluid. \\nThe associated reference is:\\nhttps://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538325/\",\n71:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-02T05:43:35Z\",\n72:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n73:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n74:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n75:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n76:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-3982262861\",\n77:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n78:     },\n79:     {\n80:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87tXMny\",\n81:       \"author\": {\n82:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n83:       },\n84:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n85:       \"body\": \"## Proposed Parent Term and Definitions for Salivary Gland Ducto-Acinar Units\\n\\n@zhengj2007 Thank you for the detailed clarifications! Based on the information you provided and my review of the UBERON ontology structure, here is my proposal.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Background: Ontological Modeling\\n\\nI reviewed analogous structures in UBERON for guidance:\\n- **Mammary gland lobule** (UBERON:0001912): `is_a lobule` (UBERON:0009911), `part_of mammary gland`, contains both secretory alveoli and lactiferous ducts\\n- **Liver lobule** (UBERON:0004647): `is_a organ part`, `part_of liver parenchyma`  \\n- **Nephron** (UBERON:0001285): the functional unit of the kidney, `is_a organ part`, `part_of uriniferous tubule`\\n\\nThe ducto-acinar unit (salivon) is the direct salivary gland equivalent of the mammary gland lobule: a repeating functional module within the gland that integrates both secretory (acinar) and ductal compartments, together with supportive stromal and vascular elements. I therefore propose it be modeled similarly as `is_a lobule` (UBERON:0009911).\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Proposed Term Hierarchy\\n\\n#### Generic parent term (NEW):\\n\\n**Label:** salivary gland ducto-acinar unit  \\n**Synonym (EXACT):** salivon  \\n**Synonym (RELATED):** salivary gland ducto-acinar  \\n**is_a:** UBERON:0009911 ! lobule  \\n**part_of:** UBERON:0001044 ! saliva-secreting gland  \\n**Definition:**  \\n> \\\"A lobule of a salivary gland consisting of secretory acini together with their contiguous ductal segments, including the intercalated duct and striated duct, together with associated myoepithelial cells, stromal tissue, and vasculature. This structural-functional unit is responsible for the production of primary saliva by the acinar cells and its ionic modification during transit through the ductal segments.\\\" [PMID:24862590, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538325/]\\n\\n**Comment:** Also known as the \\\"salivon\\\" in classical salivary physiology literature. The three major salivary glands (... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n86:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-02T05:50:04Z\",\n87:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n88:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n89:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n90:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n91:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-3982281202\",\n92:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n93:     },\n94:     {\n95:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87tlSY6\",\n96:       \"author\": {\n97:         \"login\": \"zhengj2007\"\n98:       },\n99:       \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n100:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please propose UBERON parent term and definition of \\\"gingival attachment\\\" based on the information I provided:\\n\\nYou have questions about the term \\\"gingival attachment\\\".\\nThe response from HRA domain experts are:\\nFor the gingival attachment term, the intended meaning corresponds to the entire dentogingival/periodontal attachment apparatus. Thus, among the proposed options, the closest answer is (c): the entire attachment apparatus. We agree that “gingival attachment” can be ambiguous in periodontal anatomy. If helpful for ontology precision, we would support renaming or clarifying the label to reflect that this represents a multi-tissue anatomical complex rather than gingival epithelium alone (which is already represented by UBERON:0001949). \\n\\nAdditionally, I obtained the following information via a Google search:\\nAttached gingiva is the firm, resilient, keratinized gum tissue bound directly to the underlying alveolar bone and cementum, extending from the free gingiva to the mucogingival junction. \\nAssociated references:\\nhttps://pmc.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/articles/PMC3532730/\\nhttps://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/3462203/\\n\\n\",\n101:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-02T17:57:12Z\",\n102:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n103:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n104:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n105:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n106:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-3985974842\",\n107:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n108:     },\n109:     {\n110:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87tlXst\",\n111:       \"author\": {\n112:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n113:       },\n114:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n115:       \"body\": \"## Proposed Parent Term and Definition for \\\"Gingival Attachment\\\"\\n\\n@zhengj2007 Thank you for the clarifications and additional references. After reviewing the existing UBERON terms and the provided references, here is my analysis and proposal.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Important Terminological Distinction\\n\\nBefore proposing a definition, I need to flag a key ambiguity in the information provided:\\n\\nThe HRA domain experts stated that the intended concept is **option (c): the entire dentogingival/periodontal attachment apparatus** (junctional epithelium + connective tissue attachment + cementum surface).\\n\\nHowever, the Google search results and the references provided describe a **different concept**: **\\\"attached gingiva\\\"** — the firm, keratinized portion of the gingiva tightly bound to alveolar bone and cementum, delimited coronally by the free gingival groove and apically by the mucogingival junction.\\n\\nThe two PMC/PMID references provided:\\n- **PMC3532730** (Wennström et al. study): explicitly about width of **attached gingiva**\\n- **PMID:3462203** (Benson et al.): about reformation of the **supracrestal attachment unit** after crown placement — a third concept relating to the biologic width\\n\\nThese references do not describe the \\\"entire dentogingival/periodontal attachment apparatus\\\" as described by the HRA experts.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Existing UBERON Terms to Be Aware Of\\n\\n| UBERON ID | Name | Notes |\\n|-----------|------|-------|\\n| UBERON:0001828 | gingiva | The parent term; fibrous investing tissue with keratinized epithelium surrounding a tooth |\\n| UBERON:0001949 | gingival epithelium | Stratified squamous epithelium of the gingiva (part_of gingiva) |\\n| UBERON:0035149 | **gingival epithelial attachment** | Anatomical junction; part_of gingival epithelium; located_in gingival groove |\\n| UBERON:0001758 | periodontium | The entire tooth-supporting apparatus (PDL + gingivae + cementum + alveolar bone) |\\n| UBERON:0035967 | alveolar mucosa | \\\"The muc... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n116:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-02T18:01:42Z\",\n117:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n118:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n119:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n120:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n121:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-3985996589\",\n122:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n123:     },\n124:     {\n125:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87vM2aM\",\n126:       \"author\": {\n127:         \"login\": \"nicolevasilevsky\"\n128:       },\n129:       \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n130:       \"body\": \"I will work on this @zhengj2007 (we discussed this on an HRA call)\",\n131:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-06T17:47:50Z\",\n132:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n133:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n134:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n135:       \"reactionGroups\": [\n136:         {\n137:           \"content\": \"THUMBS_UP\",\n138:           \"users\": {\n139:             \"totalCount\": 1\n140:           }\n141:         }\n142:       ],\n143:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-4013123212\",\n144:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n145:     },\n146:     {\n147:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87vNgeS\",\n148:       \"author\": {\n149:         \"login\": \"zhengj2007\"\n150:       },\n151:       \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n152:       \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please propose UBERON parent term and definition of \\\"gingival attachment\\\" again.\\n\\nYou have questions about the term \\\"gingival attachment\\\".\\nThe response from HRA domain experts are:\\nFor the gingival attachment term, the intended meaning corresponds to the entire dentogingival/periodontal attachment apparatus. Thus, among the proposed options, the closest answer is (c): the entire attachment apparatus. We agree that “gingival attachment” can be ambiguous in periodontal anatomy. If helpful for ontology precision, we would support renaming or clarifying the label to reflect that this represents a multi-tissue anatomical complex rather than gingival epithelium alone (which is already represented by UBERON:0001949).\",\n153:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-06T18:23:05Z\",\n154:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n155:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n156:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n157:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n158:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-4013295506\",\n159:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n160:     },\n161:     {\n162:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87vNkND\",\n163:       \"author\": {\n164:         \"login\": \"dragon-ai-agent\"\n165:       },\n166:       \"authorAssociation\": \"COLLABORATOR\",\n167:       \"body\": \"## Revised Proposal for \\\\\\\"gingival attachment\\\\\\\"\\n\\n@zhengj2007 Thank you for clarifying. Given the confirmed intent — **the entire dentogingival/periodontal attachment apparatus, a multi-tissue complex** — here is my revised proposal.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Context: What's already in UBERON\\n\\n| UBERON ID | Name | Notes |\\n|-----------|------|-------|\\n| UBERON:0001828 | gingiva | Fibrous investing tissue with keratinized epithelium surrounding a tooth; the requested parent |\\n| UBERON:0001758 | periodontium | Broader: PDL + gingivae + cementum + alveolar bone |\\n| UBERON:0001949 | gingival epithelium | Stratified squamous epithelium of the gingiva |\\n| UBERON:0035149 | gingival epithelial attachment | Only the epithelial component; is_a anatomical junction, part_of gingival epithelium |\\n\\nNo existing UBERON term captures the **full multi-tissue attachment complex** (epithelium + connective tissue + vasculature/stroma) anchoring the gingiva to the tooth.\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Proposed New Term\\n\\n**Preferred label:** dentogingival junction  \\n**Synonym (RELATED):** gingival attachment  \\n**Synonym (RELATED):** dentogingival complex  \\n**Synonym (RELATED):** supracrestal tissue attachment  \\n\\n**is_a:** UBERON:0000479 ! tissue  \\n**part_of:** UBERON:0001828 ! gingiva  \\n\\n**Proposed definition:**\\n> \\\\\\\"A multi-tissue anatomical complex that constitutes the attachment zone between the gingival tissue and the tooth surface, comprising the junctional epithelium, the supracrestal connective tissue attachment fibers, and supporting stromal and vascular elements. This structure seals the periodontal space from the oral cavity and serves as the primary physical and biological interface anchoring the free and attached gingiva to the tooth.\\\\\\\" [PMID:38876998, ISBN:9780323096300]\\n\\n(ISBN:9780323096300 = Ten Cate's Oral Histology, 8th ed., which describes the dentogingival junction in detail)\\n\\n---\\n\\n### Rationale for label choice\\n\\nI propose **\\\\\\\"dentogingival juncti... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n168:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-06T18:26:41Z\",\n169:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n170:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n171:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n172:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n173:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-4013310787\",\n174:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n175:     },\n176:     {\n177:       \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87vPgUz\",\n178:       \"author\": {\n179:         \"login\": \"zhengj2007\"\n180:       },\n181:       \"authorAssociation\": \"NONE\",\n182:       \"body\": \"Hi @nicolevasilevsky Based on chatting with @dragon-ai-agent (previous comments), here are proposed terms with definitions. I highlighted our original requested term labels in bold font. \\n\\nGeneric parent term **ducto-acinar** (NEW, added for 3 terms needed by HuBMAP):\\nLabel: salivary gland ducto-acinar unit\\nSynonym (EXACT): salivon\\nSynonym (RELATED): salivary gland ducto-acinar\\nis_a: UBERON:0009911 ! lobule\\npart_of: UBERON:0001044 ! saliva-secreting gland\\nDefinition:\\n\\n\\\"A lobule of a salivary gland consisting of secretory acini together with their contiguous ductal segments, including the intercalated duct and striated duct, together with associated myoepithelial cells, stromal tissue, and vasculature. This structural-functional unit is responsible for the production of primary saliva by the acinar cells and its ionic modification during transit through the ductal segments.\\\" [PMID:24862590, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538325/]\\nComment: Also known as the \\\"salivon\\\" in classical salivary physiology literature. The three major salivary glands (parotid, submandibular, sublingual) contain gland-specific variants of this unit that differ in acinar cell composition (serous vs. mucous vs. mixed).\\n\\n3 terms as children of \\\"salivary gland ducto-acinar unit\\\" (**ducto-acinar**) requested by Griffin:\\n\\n1. parotid gland ducto-acinar unit (**parotid gland ducto-acinar**)\\nLabel: parotid gland ducto-acinar unit\\nSynonym (RELATED): parotid gland ducto-acinar\\nis_a: salivary gland ducto-acinar unit (new term above)\\npart_of: UBERON:0001831 ! parotid gland\\nDefinition:\\n\\n\\\"A salivary gland ducto-acinar unit that is part of the parotid gland, consisting of purely serous acini together with their contiguous intercalated and striated ductal segments, and associated myoepithelial cells, stromal tissue, and vasculature. This unit produces a watery, protein-rich serous saliva.\\\" [PMID:24862590, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538325/]\\n\\n2. s... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n183:       \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-06T19:54:58Z\",\n184:       \"includesCreatedEdit\": false,\n185:       \"isMinimized\": false,\n186:       \"minimizedReason\": \"\",\n187:       \"reactionGroups\": [],\n188:       \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657#issuecomment-4013819187\",\n189:       \"viewerDidAuthor\": false\n190:     }\n191:   ],\n192:   \"title\": \"New term requests by HRA/HuBMAP\",\n193:   \"url\": \"https://github.com/obophenotype/uberon/issues/3657\"\n194: }\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"body\": \"**Preferred term label:**\\nparotid gland ducto-acinar\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nEaster QT, et al. Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis. Nat Commun. 2024 Jun 14;15(1):5016. doi: 10.1038/s41467-024-49037-y. PMID: 38876998; PMCID: PMC11178863; https://doi.org/10.48539/HBM632.GTVR.643\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\nUBERON:0001831  parotid gland\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n0000-0002-2999-0103\\n\\n---------------\\n**Preferred term label:**\\ngingival attachment\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nEaster QT, et al. Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis. Nat Commun. 2024 Jun 14;15(1):5016. doi: 10.1038/s41467-024-49037-y. PMID: 38876998; PMCID: PMC11178863; https://doi.org/10.48539/HBM632.GTVR.643\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\nUBERON:0001828  gingiva\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n0000-0002-2999-0103\\n\\n---------------\\n**Preferred term label:**\\nsublingual gland ducto-acinar\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nEaster QT, et al. Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis. Nat Commun. 2024 Jun 14;15(1):5016. doi: 10.1038/s41467-024-49037-y. PMID: 38876998; PMCID: PMC11178863; https://doi.org/10.48539/HBM632.GTVR.643\\n\\n**Parent term (use https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols/ontologies/uberon)**\\nUBERON:0001832  sublingual gland\\n\\n**Your nano-attribution (ORCID)**\\n0000-0002-2999-0103\\n\\n---------------\\n**Preferred term label:**\\nsubmandibular gland ducto-acinar\\n\\n**Synonyms**\\n\\n**Definition (free text, please give PubMed ID)**\\nEaster QT, et al. Single-cell and spatially resolved interactomics of tooth-associated keratinocytes in periodontitis. Nat Commun. 2024 Jun 14;15(1):5016. doi: 10.10... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n  \"comments\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"IC_kwDOAAidd87mOcu4\",\n      \"author\": {\n        \"login\": \"cmungall\"\n      },\n      \"authorAssociation\": \"MEMBER\",\n      \"body\": \"@dragon-ai-agent please analyze these terms, provide a plan for how you will add them to the ontology, check for existing naming conventions and design patterns for similar terms\",\n      \"createdAt\": \"2026-02-06T20:59:48Z\",