ucous acini (with minor serous demilunes) together with their contiguous ductal segments, and associated myoepithelial cells, stromal tissue, and vasculature. This unit produces a viscous, mucin-rich saliva.\" [PMID:24862590, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538325/]\n\n---\n\n**3. submandibular gland ducto-acinar unit**  \n**Label:** submandibular gland ducto-acinar unit  \n**Synonym (RELATED):** submandibular gland ducto-acinar  \n**is_a:** salivary gland ducto-acinar unit (new term above)  \n**part_of:** UBERON:0001736 ! submandibular gland  \n**Definition:**  \n> \"A salivary gland ducto-acinar unit that is part of the submandibular gland, consisting of a mixture of predominantly serous acini (approximately 90%) with a minority of mucous acini, together with their contiguous ductal segments, and associated myoepithelial cells, stromal tissue, and vasculature. This unit produces a mixed serous-mucous saliva.\" [PMID:24862590, https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538325/]\n\n---\n\n### Notes and Questions\n\n1. **Label format:** I am proposing to use \"ducto-acinar unit\" rather than just \"ducto-acinar\" as the label, since this makes it clear we are defining an anatomical structure (a unit), not an adjective. The requested names (\"parotid gland ducto-acinar\" etc.) would be included as RELATED synonyms. Does this naming work for HRA data annotation purposes?\n\n2. **References:** For salivary gland-specific ducto-acinar composition, I used:\n   - PMID:24862590 (Holmberg & Hoffman 2014, *Monogr Oral Sci* - salivary gland anatomy/biogenesis)\n   - https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK538325/ (StatPearls: Anatomy, Salivary Glands)\n   - The HBM dataset DOI (https://doi.org/10.48539/HBM632.GTVR.643) can be added as an xref\n   \n3. **Stromal/vascular components:** The text definitions above mention stroma and vasculature, consistent with the FTU definition you provided. However, for the OWL logical definition, I would keep the intersection_of axioms simpler 