y the acinar cells and its ionic modification during transit through the ductal segments.\" [PMID:24862590, PMID:30855909]\ncomment: Also known as the salivon in classical salivary physiology literature. The three major salivary glands (parotid, submandibular, sublingual) contain gland-specific variants of this unit that differ in acinar cell composition.\nsubset: added_by_HRA\nsynonym: \"salivary gland ducto-acinar\" RELATED []\nsynonym: \"salivon\" EXACT []\nis_a: UBERON:0009911 ! lobule\nrelationship: dc-contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2999-0103","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo","time":{"start":1778977017309,"end":1778977017623}},"id":"prt_e334b0aec0010Qi4IQNy6YQ4QU","sessionID":"ses_1ccb84d98ffeWH3ShOq9EHPmcq","messageID":"msg_e334b03ae001qbW1UkZ42B4S8I"}}
